    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That tapping sound is likely called water hammer, which happens when water rushing from the pipes hits metal fixtures or bends instead of flowing smoothly. It's not normal for a standard sink faucet drip but is very common in older homes where the water pressure is too high when the valve closes. Installing a small bundle of plumbing tape at the stem or using a water hammer arrestor on the supply line can stop the noise and prevent pipe damage in the future.",
